  "original_title": "\u0d87\u0db8\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dd4 \u0da7\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dbb\u0dae\u0dba\u0dda \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dd2 \u0dc3\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db8\u0dab\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca 51\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db8\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "51 migrants killed in US truck crash",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The death toll from a truck crash in Texas on Monday has risen to 51, foreign reports say.",
        "Of those killed, 27 were identified as Mexicans, Mexican Consul General in San Antonio Ruben Minute Sanata told a news conference Tuesday. .",
        "He added that 13 others, including three Mexicans, had been hospitalized.",
        "The U.S. is enforcing the lawsuit against two suspects who are Mexican nationals and say they were residents of the United States.",
        "A third suspect, described as a U.S. citizen who drove the truck, was also arrested and is expected to be charged, but he was hospitalized Tuesday evening, a Mexican official said."
      ],
